FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - BULGARIA (09): (BURGAS) UPDATE
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Wed 19 Jan 2011
Source: Novinite.com, Sofia News Agency [edited]
<http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=124306>


The European Commission is contented with the measures that Bulgaria
has taken to fight the foot-and-mouth disease [FMD] in the village of
Rezovo and is ready to provide full technical and financial support,
the Bulgarian Agriculture Ministry announced.

On Wednesday [19 Jan 2011], the Bulgarian agriculture minister,
Miroslav Naydenov, visited Rezovo, where the authorities localized a
2nd outbreak of FMD, in addition to the cases in the nearby village of
Kosti in the Burgas District.

In Rezovo, 200 animals owned by 11 farmers have already been slaughtered.

"The owners will receive the 1st compensations of BGN 300 [approx. USD
206] within days. They will also receive additional compensations for
the loss of milk yield because of the 3-month quarantine, which would
prevent them from breeding animals," Naydenov said.

The minister pointed out that the farmers from Kosti have already
received their 1st compensations of BGN 300.

A 3-month quarantine was declared in Rezovo. People who do not live in
the village would not be allowed to pass in a radius of 4 km [2.5 mi].
All vehicles leaving the area will be disinfected.

At the beginning of January [2011], the 1st case of FMD in Bulgaria in
the past 12 years was announced . It was found in a wild boar that has
been killed in the region of the southeastern city of Burgas.

--
